        <p>Hey, I'm Sarrick Shiflett. The aspect of coding that captures my soul is the makers mindset. The thrill of bringing something in the mind to life, and the pride that comes with it. Ideas come to life that have never been and knowing they’re useful or just plain fun has an incredibly satisfying feeling to it and I've found very few things come close.</p>

        <p>I started my coding journey a few years ago with iOS, specifically Apple's new language, Swift, while working at a local FedEx. I quickly saw the potential to simplify everyday tasks, like my traffic app that scans for the perfect time to leave for work, saving me so much time in traffic! The thrill of building tools that simplify or ease everyday dilemmas keeps me hooked.</p>

        <p>I’ve learned a bunch of programming languages since then, each one adding new skills and principles. I enjoy the challenge of picking up new technologies and solving problems.</p>
